      },
      "date": "2012-12-04 14:40:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Alex,\n\nI think I understand and agree.  But just to clarify, are you saying:\n\n1) This patch would be approved if in addition it created the symlinks .../obdfilter/lustre-OSTXXXX/brw_stats -> .../osd-xxx/lustre-OSTXXXX/brw_stats.\n\n2) We should restore the code that maintains filter_obd's struct brw_stats *fo_filter_stats member.\n\n3) Other.\n\nNote: the maintenance of filter_obd's struct brw_stats *fo_filter_stats was removed some time ago by OSD restructuring, as was the maintenance of the per NID brw_stats.  Patch set 1 only removes the /proc files displaying these brw_stats plus some now dead code and structure members.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "54d776cefe101fa80e57eb5b3444737f59e17c57",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-04 15:06:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n) This patch would be approved if in addition it created the symlinks .../obdfilter/lustre-OSTXXXX/brw_stats -> .../osd-xxx/lustre-OSTXXXX/brw_stats.\n2) We should restore the code that maintains filter_obd's struct brw_stats *fo_filter_stats member.\n3) Other.\nNote: the maintenance of filter_obd's struct brw_stats *fo_filter_stats was removed some time ago by OSD restructuring, as was the maintenance of the per NID brw_stats. Patch set 1 only removes the /proc files displaying these brw_stats plus some now dead code and structure members.\n\nsorry for confusion..  I meant just symlinks, IOW (1). \n\nstrictly speaking I'm fine with removal of unused code, but it'd be better (imho) if the same patch creates symlinks as well. if you're planning to do symlinks in a subsequent patch, that's fine as well.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ea41a4dd579c079d2234bc1ada38105cb8d5cf62",
      "author": {
