    {
      "id": "726f40ab7e0c98d0f94500b9a5cdcca11d4353d7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-14 15:12:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\ntechnically the patch looks good, but i'm not sure we actually want to get rid of the stats. i think you need andreas to approve this.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "874740916128008906769be2350611f071c111c6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-14 19:30:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> technically the patch looks good, but i'm not sure we actually want to get rid of the stats.\n\nWe (meaning you ;)) got rid of the stats during OSD restructuring. This just removes some pointless proc files and struct fields. There is also very little chance of us restoring these stats to their former functionality. In osd-ldiskfs we are not passing exp down to osd_do_bio(). In osd-zfs, how can we compute \"disk fragmented I/Os\" or \"discontiguous pages\"?\n\nNote that we still maintain per-export {read,write}_bytes counters in ofd and this patch does not change that.\n\n # cat /proc/fs/lustre/obdfilter/lustre-OST0000/exports/0\\@lo/stats\nsnapshot_time             1360870157.602754 secs.usecs\nread_bytes                11 samples [bytes] 4096 1048576 10485760\nwrite_bytes               10 samples [bytes] 1048576 1048576 10485760\nget_info                  6 samples [reqs]\ncreate                    4 samples [reqs]\nsync                      1 samples [reqs]\npreprw                    21 samples [reqs]\ncommitrw                  21 samples [reqs]\nping                      295 samples [reqs]",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "a5701502d798a0ab651dd40ed7906e88923926e2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
